dc_title_s: [Geological Survey of England and Wales : one inch to the mile map. New Series.] Anglesey, drift, sheets 92, 93, and parts of 94, 105 & 106
dc_description_s: Geological Survey of Great Britain. Great Britain. Geological Survey of England and Wales. Sheets 92,93/parts of 94,105,106 drift. Great Britain. Ordnance Survey of England. North Decimal Degree 53.433300. South Decimal Degree 53.1333. East Decimal Degree -4.0167. West Decimal Degree -4.7000. In upper left margin: Ordnance Survey of Great Britain. Relief shown by contour interval and spot heights.Transverse Mercator projection. National grid system. Depth shown by contour intervals. "Original geological survey on the one-inch scale. Published on sheets 77 & 78 Old Series, 1852. Re-surveyed on the six-inch scale by Edward Greenly, Published with Drift 1920.".
dc_publisher_s: [Southampton ; Chessington, Surrey] : Director General, Ordnance Survey, 1920.
